pesticide.PPE: Long-sleeved shirt and long pants; Chemical-resistant gloves made of barrier laminate, butyl rubber (>14 mils), nitrile rubber (>14 mils), neoprene rubber (>14 mils), polyvinyl chloride (PVC) (>14 mils), or viton (>14 mils); Shoes plus socks; Protective eyewear for mixers and loaders; Discard clothing and other absorbent materials heavily contaminated with concentrate; Follow manufacturer’s instructions for cleaning/maintaining PPE; Keep and wash PPE separately from other laundry

Safety_Information.general_Info: WARNING. May be fatal if swallowed. Causes moderate eye irritation. Avoid contact with eyes or clothing. Wash thoroughly with soap and water after handling and before eating, drinking, chewing gum, using tobacco, or using the toilet.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15-20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after the first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing eye. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Call a poison control center or doctor immediately for treatment advice. Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow. DO NOT induce vomiting unless told to do so by a poison control center or doctor. DO NOT give anything by mouth to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: This product is a pyrethroid. If large amounts have been ingested, the stomach and intestines should be evacuated. Treatment is symptomatic and supportive. Digestible fats, oils, or alcohol may increase absorption and so should be avoided.

Target_Disease_Pest.name: Corn rootworm larvae (Northern, Southern and Western)
